repo.name: mineflayer

body:
Been updating mineflayer in order to bring 1.7 support (and to find bugs in node-minecraft-protocol 1.7). Currently, all the packet definitions in the plugins have been updated to use the packet name, and the fields were modified to reflect new names when they changed. All tests pass, but it's almost a guarantee that there is still a bunch of bugs left here and there. I'll be testing things left and right. 

Burger is currently broken with 1.7 and all. I'll try to fix it, but no guarantees can be made. 

Also, note that the package.json currently uses git URL instead of version for node-minecraft-protocol due to changes not yet pushed to NPM. 

What needs fixing : 
- [x] Chat module parsing needs a lot of improvement. It should recursively parse the "with" and extras.
- [x] Navigation is currently broken. It seems like the physics module isn't triggered at all.
- [x] Bot is unable to respawn
- ~~Sometimes, generally after teleporting, entities are removed from the entity list when they shouldn't be.~~ Moved to: #181

(probably a lot more, list will grow as I find more bugs).

3rd party states : 
- Navigate doesn't work.
- Radar works partially, navigation doesn't work.

Didn't test the rest, those are the top two priority for me, since they test the most essential part of the bot.

----
#### Issue Dependency Graph
![Issue Dependency](http://i.imgur.com/pDySd9S.png)

Has most the issues for the Stable 1.7 milestone, just to give some visual overview what needs to be done

-NeverCast

commit.message: Update to 1.7 chat message, impl. ChatMessage class

Refresh ChatMessage class to be recursive

Split 1.6 and 1.7 implementation in chat plugin
Introduce new bot event, 'message'.

Quick message event fix

1.6 will still emit the same events as before
1.7 will emit a ChatMessage object with 'message'.
'chat' and 'whisper' work as expected

Fix parsing, with is optional with translate

Example: Changing game mode.

More fixes towards 1.7 compliance, success!

Physics now working, logging in now working, movement NOW WORKING!

Some old API breaking changes

* bot.players is now a lookup function, the caching of entities was bad.
* entity's now have an isValid property, plugins should check this.
Ignore an entity if it's not valid (Set to false when destroyed)
* bot.players takes a string, regular expression or function to filter
your lookups, quite handy. No argument will return all players. Most
arguments will return an Array of entities, except for a String when it
matches exactly to a player's name, in which case just that player is
returned.
* Player Entities are now not a thing, they are just entities, player
information is stored in the entity property, entity.playerInfo. EG.
entity.playerInfo.ping

Reverted bot.players, added bot.findPlayers

* Remove some debugging stuff
* Added inventory assertion
* Previous search function changed to bot.findPlayers
* Aliases as bot.findPlayer
* bot.players returned to previous functionality to support entities
that are out of range.]

Fix broken heldItem/selectedSlot

* Reimplement equiping by type

Merge pull request #2 from nevercast/feature-1.7

Merge nevercast/feature-1.7
